My ultimate goal for the warrior I have is to be the MT on the higher end raids my guild is moving toward. Thus I'm mainly concentrating on AC, and have gotten up to 1020ish unbuffed at level 40 (and will continue to grow from there, given the various pieces of recommended armor I have that don't max out until level 45). I still have a few weak spot (upgrade to my belt for a big one, and higher end haste is definately in order), but for the most part I'm doing pretty well for my level.<br>
<br>
But one of the big issues I have is with my off hand weapon. I'm definately going to be upgrading it in the near future, and would really appreciate some advice on what to go with. As far as plat goes, I'm mainly looking for 'bang for buck.' While I'd be willing to shell out around 20k if the weapon was truly worth it, I'd probably go with a lower end weapon if it was substantially cheaper and nearly as effective, especially because I do a few more upgrades to go before I'm satisfied.<br>
<br>
One of the weapons I've been looking at is the LSoEE, going for around 8 to 10k on Prexus right now. The AC on it (15) is very very nice, and would probably bring my warrior to just under 1100 AC with a level 39 cleric buff (currently at 1060 with valor and the 39 ac buff). The ratio itself is decent enough, I suppose, but nothing *huge*.<br>
<br>
So what do you think? I currently use a Frostbringer in my main hand for aggro. Would I be better off searching for a better main hand weapon? Or is there a really nice off hander that I'm over looking? Or should I perhaps save up and get some higher end haste? And, in your opinion, is a LSoEE worth about 10k?<br>
<br>
